# InTheMoment — project rules

InTheMoment is a native SwiftUI iOS app (artists/event companies post photos &
videos; fans browse and download). It has three Swift parts that share models:

- `Sources/InTheMomentCore/` — shared models + logic (NO UIKit/SwiftUI/Vapor). Built on Linux & Apple.
- `App/InTheMoment/` — SwiftUI app + `AppModel` + services. Built only in Xcode on macOS.
- `Server/` — Vapor + Fluent + SQLite backend. Reuses `InTheMomentCore`.

## Must follow

- **Do NOT hand-edit `InTheMoment.xcodeproj`.** It is generated from `project.yml`
  via XcodeGen. Add/rename files on disk, then run `xcodegen generate` and commit
  the result.
- **`Creator` / `Event` / `MediaItem` are defined once** in `InTheMomentCore` and
  used by both the app and the server. Never duplicate or fork them.
- **Keep `Sources/InTheMomentCore` platform-agnostic** — no `import SwiftUI`,
  `import UIKit`, or `import Vapor` there.
- **Views never do networking.** Views → `AppModel` → a store protocol. Add logic
  to a store or `AppModel`, not to a `View`.
- **All JSON dates are ISO-8601.** App, `APIEventStore`, and server must stay in sync.
- **Don't commit secrets.** `JWT_SECRET` is an env var; auth tokens live in the Keychain.

## Backend architecture

Each data concern is its own protocol with an in-memory impl (tests/previews) and
a REST impl (production), all talking through an injectable `HTTPTransport` wrapped
in `AuthenticatedTransport` to attach the bearer token:

- `EventStore` — events/media. `InMemoryEventStore`, `FileEventStore` (on-device),
  `APIEventStore` (default).
- `FanPreferencesStore` — favorites/follows. `File…` (anonymous) ↔ `API…` (signed in).
- `AnalyticsStore` — views/downloads. Recording is anonymous; reading is creator-only.
- `SocialStore` — comments/likes. Reads are public; writes require a token; a
  comment is deletable by its author or the event's owning creator.

## Auth

There is one account type. `/auth/register` creates an account with a `Creator`
profile and `/auth/login` returns `{ token, creator? }`; `creator` is optional
only for older accounts without a profile. Read routes are public; event/creator
writes require a token with the owned creator profile and enforce per-creator
ownership (derived from the token, not the body). Auth responses include the
`userId`/`id`. Favorites/follows sync per-account via `/me/preferences`,
`/me/favorites/{id}`, `/me/follows/{id}`; the app uses `APIFanPreferencesStore`
when signed in and `FileFanPreferencesStore` when anonymous. See
`CONTRIBUTING.md` for the full REST reference (events, fan prefs, comments/likes,
analytics).

## Verifying changes

```bash
swift build && swift test     # core — always
cd Server && swift build      # server
xcodegen generate             # after any App/ file change
```

The iOS app target is verified in Xcode on macOS (not in CI).
